res_description: A popular floating restaurant in Tayabas City, known for it's native-style huts over fishponds, it serves fresh Filipino food and traditional dishes, often enjoyed kamayan style (eating with hands) in a relaxing nature inspired setting

A famous floating restaurant experience where guests dine in nipa huts on a large pond, enjoying fresh Filipino dishes, especially seafood, often catching their own tilapia for cooking, offering a unique, relaxing, native ambiance.

Corneliaâ€™s Plate is a restaurant in Tayabas City known for its fantastic view of both the Basilica of St. Michael the Archangel and the Mt. Banahaw from afar. The place is situated on a rooftop, offering al fresco dining for everyone who wants to enjoy some good food while feasting their eyes on a great view.
Serving popular Asian dishes and Filipino staples to our local.

A popular Filipino restaurant chain, originating from Lucban, Quezon, known for its vibrant, fiesta-themed ambiance inspired by the local Pahiyas Festival, serving authentic Quezon province dishes like Pancit Lucban (also Pancit Habhab), Longganisang Lucban, Hardinera, Sisig, and their signature overloaded pizzas, offering a festive taste of local Filipino culture and cuisine in an extensive, family-friendly setting.

Established in 1943, Rodillas Restaurant is a casual, family-friendly restaurant in Tayabas, Quezon, Philippines. It has been serving delicious Filipino food for many years and is known for its affordable prices and friendly service. The restaurant is open for breakfast, lunch, and dinner, and also offers brunch. Some of the popular dishes on the menu includes laing and hardinera.
Rodillas Restaurant is also famous for its Yema Cake, a yellow sponge cake with a gooey caramel topping.
A well-known restaurant in City of Tayabas serving delicious local cusine with a good ambiance place.
